{
  "stem": "11274.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were-- but they were wearing locks-- I think you call them locks-- the peyos and beards.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then they locked up the temple-- they didn't burn the temple-- locked up the temple after all the books were burning.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then they were making remarks to the Jews and putting them down, and calling them names and everything, while they were doing it too.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If everything-- after everything was burnt, Father came home, and I've never seen my father before-- [CRYING] I've never seen him like this.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He looked like the whole world was-- it was ended for him.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[CRYING] But we were happy that he came home, that he was still alive.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So we weren't as stressed as he was, but I felt sorry, and I felt terrible for him.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And so did Mom and Danka.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then my sister, [INAUDIBLE] before [? that, ?] she'll tell you now, again, escaped to Czechoslovakia with her little boy, to have the surgery that was necessary to remove his tonsils.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And-- excuse me.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[DRINKS] And then they forbid us-- and came harvest time, which it was in September, it was very close to it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We had to come to work anyway.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we had planted potatoes, and all those greens [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And the usually thing was that the Jewish people had some, like migrant workers here, some farmers, young people, would hire themselves out to work for-- for everybody, for gentiles, and for the Jewish farmers that-- that had, for money, to pay them by day.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And they were doing the harvest work.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The-- because we-- we were just the two of us, the two girls.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And my father and mother were already older-- older people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we hired them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were helping.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
